Contains input files to simulate DNS of channel flow at Re_tau=180. All details are taken from the following paper.

John Kim,  Parviz Moin, and Robert Moser, Turbulence statistics in fully developed channel flow at low Reynolds number, Journal of Fluid Mechanics,
DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0022112087000892

Works with version number 1143 of Nek5000.
To modify the averaging procedure, in kmm.upar file change the following

 STAT_COMP --- Once in these number of iterations, averaging is computed
 STAT_OUTP --- Once in these number of iterations, averaging files are written
